            "description": "Intercultural internship as part of the Minor program International Entrepreneurship and Development, together with two other students from different disciplines.\n\nPart 1 in Oltepesi, in Masai countryside. Project involved introducing an evaporative-cooling unit, allowing refrigeration by consuming water instead of electricity.\n\nPart 2 in Matunda, near Kitale at the Loreto Convent girls boarding High School. Project included a case study on how to improve the schools resource management. The scope of the project covered waste conversion to bio-gas, greenhouse and administration improvement at the school farm, rainwater harvesting and possibilities for renewable energy.\n\nThe intercultural Internship was a great personal development. Working in a country with such a different culture in an environment I am not accustomed to was an interesting challenge. I have also developed my entrepreneurial skills together with my intercultural communication skills. The stay in Kenya has sparked an interest for complex development problems.\n\n",
