            "description": "A 10 day challenge organised by the Dutch embassy in South-Africa together with TomTom and IBM and other partners. The challenge was part of the HouseOfTheFuture festival, hosted in Johannesburg, where Dutch and South-African entrepreneurs work together to improve the Health-, Transport-, Agriculture-, Water- and Energy- sector. \n\n30 motivated interdisciplinary students from two Dutch and 2 South-African universities worked together in five teams on solutions for problems in one of the five sectors. We received mentorship and intensive business courses on entrepreneurship from local experts. The results of the projects were pitched on two occasions. Once for a grand jury of CEO\u2019s from sponsors and partners and a second time for the Dutch PM and his trade delegates. My project was in the Energy sector and I was elected by my team to pitch the second pitch for the Dutch PM\n",
